WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.360
To cement sand quickly, we need the enzyme on

2
00:00:02.460 --> 00:00:04.876
the OUTSIDE of the cell, where the calcium and

3
00:00:04.976 --> 00:00:07.501
carbon dioxide are. Getting it there is a relay.

4
00:00:09.800 --> 00:00:12.903
First, export the enzyme through the wall. Then it must

5
00:00:13.003 --> 00:00:16.107
fold correctly. Then it must be stapled to the surface.

6
00:00:16.207 --> 00:00:18.320
Each step only works part of the time.

7
00:00:19.900 --> 00:00:22.810
So the fraction that ends up active on the surface is those

8
00:00:22.910 --> 00:00:26.382
chances multiplied together — never all of them, but enough to matter.

9
00:00:27.266 --> 00:00:30.980
Why go to all this trouble? Because carbonic anhydrase speeds the

10
00:00:31.080 --> 00:00:35.087
key reaction — carbon dioxide into bicarbonate — about a million-fold.

11
00:00:35.187 --> 00:00:38.138
On the surface, that is where the cementing happens.

